The Minister of Transportation, Chibuke Rotimi Amaechi, yesterday said he is not a sectional aspirant. He said his presidential strength lies in his experience as a speaker, governor, chairman of the governors’ forum and now a minister of the Federal Republic of Nigeria. It’ll be injustice to Nigeria if I don’t contest – Osinbajo FG targets 21m jobs from infrastructure investment Amaechi, who spoke during his visit to the place of Olubadan of Ibadanland, Oba Lekan Balogun, said he did not belong to any geopolitical bloc as far as his presidential ambition is concerned. ‘’I’m not a Hausa/Fulani candidate, I’m not a Yoruba candidate, I’m not an Igbo candidate and I’m not even a Kalabari candidate, but a Nigerian candidate,” he said. Responding, the Olubadan of Ibadanland, said the former governor of Rivers State shares the same attribute with him on the oneness of Nigeria. He harped on the unity of the country, stressing that “irrespective of language, tribe or religion, we are all brothers and sisters.”